  "content": "\n## Archived Lists under the Interim Order Respecting Drugs, Medical Devices and Foods for a Special Dietary Purpose in Relation to COVID-19\nHealth Canada published new  amendments to the Food and Drug  Regulations in Canada Gazette, Part II on September 1, 2021. These will  create a permanent pathway for the exceptional importation and sale of  foreign-authorized drugs and medical devices into Canada in response to a  shortage. These regulations entered into force on March 2, 2022. For more  information, read the Notice of regulations amending certain  regulations concerning drugs and medical devices (shortages) .\nLinks to previous versions of the lists are provided below for information and reference purposes. For the most current versions of the lists, please refer to the Interim Order to help prevent or alleviate shortages in relation to COVID-19 .\n\n## Archive List 1: List of Drugs for Exceptional Importation and Sale\n- 2022-01-28 to 2022-03-01\n- 2021-11-23 to 2022-01-28\n- 2021-07-16 to 2021-11-23\n- 2021-07-13 to 2021-07-15\n- 2021-06-09 to 2021-07-12\n- 2021-04-29 to 2021-06-09\n- 2021-04-01 to 2021-04-29\n- 2021-03-02 to 2021-03-31\n- 2021-02-19 to 2021-03-01\n- 2021-01-28 to 2021-02-18\n- 2020-12-09 to 2021-01-27\n- 2020-12-03 to 2020-12-08\n- 2020-10-22 to 2020-12-02\n- 2020-10-14 to 2020-10-21\n- 2020-09-18 to 2020-10-13\n- 2020-09-03 to 2020-09-17\n- 2020-09-02 to 2020-09-02\n- 2020-08-21 to 2020-09-01\n- 2020-08-14 to 2020-08-20\n- 2020-08-12 to 2020-08-13\n- 2020-07-30 to 2020-08-11\n- 2020-07-28 to 2020-07-29\n- 2020-07-24 to 2020-07-27\n- 2020-07-23 to 2020-07-23\n- 2020-07-18 to 2020-07-22\n- 2020-07-16 to 2020-07-17\n- 2020-06-29 to 2020-07-15\n- 2020-06-18 to 2020-06-28\n- 2020-06-15 to 2020-06-17\n- 2020-06-11 to 2020-06-14\n- 2020-06-09 to 2020-06-10\n- 2020-06-08 to 2020-06-09\n- 2020-05-20 to 2020-06-07\n- 2020-05-15 to 2020-05-19\n- 2020-05-13 to 2020-05-14\n- 2020-05-11 to 2020-05-12\n- 2020-05-08 to 2020-05-10\n- 2020-0